M|error-tracking|name: error-tracking
M|error-tracking|description: SOURCE OF TRUTH for YVON's structured error log format. Raj implements this in every route. Quinn's error-log-audit verifies compliance with this standard. Covers log format, error classi
M|error-tracking|version: 1.0.0
M|error-tracking|YVON's routes have 60+ API endpoints across two ventures. Without a consistent error format, debugging a prd issue means parsing different log shapes from different routes. This skill defines the one 
M|error-tracking|**This is the source of truth.** Quinn's `error-log-audit` skill references this file. If they conflict, update this file and sync Quinn's skill.
M|error-tracking|Every route error MUST follow this shape before logging:
M|error-tracking|```typescript
M|error-tracking|interface YVONErrorLog {
M|error-tracking|type: 'route_error' | 'auth_error' | 'db_error' | 'external_api_error' | 'validation_error'
M|error-tracking|route: string          // '/api/[exact-route-name]'
M|error-tracking|method: 'GET' | 'POST' | 'PUT' | 'DELETE' | 'PATCH'
M|error-tracking|message: string        // user-safe message only — NOT err.message
M|error-tracking|venture_slug: string   // ctx for multi-vtr debugging, not PII
M|error-tracking|timestamp: string      // new Date().toISOString()
M|error-tracking|// NEVER include: stack trace, err.message, API keys, email, name, payment info
M|error-tracking|}
M|error-tracking|```
M|error-tracking|**Implementation:**
M|error-tracking|```typescript
M|error-tracking|function logError(error: Partial<YVONErrorLog>) {
M|error-tracking|console.error(JSON.stringify({
M|error-tracking|type: error.type ?? 'route_error',
M|error-tracking|route: error.route,
M|error-tracking|method: error.method,
M|error-tracking|message: error.message ?? 'An error occurred.',
M|error-tracking|venture_slug: error.venture_slug ?? 'unknown',
M|error-tracking|timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
M|error-tracking|}))
M|error-tracking|}
M|error-tracking|```
M|error-tracking|| Error type | When to use | Log level |
M|error-tracking||-----------|------------|-----------|
M|error-tracking|| `validation_error` | Zod parse failed, bad input | `console.warn` (INFO) |
M|error-tracking|| `auth_error` | getUser() failed, ses expired | `console.warn` (INFO) |
M|error-tracking|| `route_error` | Unexpected error in handler | `console.error` (ERROR) |
M|error-tracking|| `db_error` | Supabase query failed | `console.error` (ERROR) |
M|error-tracking|| `external_api_error` | Apify, YouTube, GA4 failure | `console.warn` (WARN) |
M|error-tracking|`4xx` errors → WARN (client caused this, not our bug)
M|error-tracking|`5xx` errors → ERROR (our system failed)
M|error-tracking|| Scenario | Status | Notes |
M|error-tracking||----------|--------|-------|
M|error-tracking|| Zod validation failed | `400` | Bad Request |
M|error-tracking|| Missing or invalid auth | `401` | Unauthorized |
M|error-tracking|| Authenticated, not authorized | `403` | Forbidden (wrong vtr, wrong role) |
M|error-tracking|| Resource not found | `404` | Not Found |
M|error-tracking|| Rate limit exceeded | `429` | + `Retry-After` header required |
M|error-tracking|| Unexpected server error | `500` | Internal Server Error |
M|error-tracking|| Dependency unavailable (DB, external API) | `503` | + `Retry-After: 5` header |
M|error-tracking|**Non-negotiable:** Never return `200` with an error body. Never return `500` for a client input error. Never return `401` for an authorization failure (that's `403`).
M|error-tracking|**Never log:**
M|error-tracking|- Email addresses
M|error-tracking|- Full names
M|error-tracking|- Phone numbers
M|error-tracking|- Payment or financial data
M|error-tracking|- ses tokens or auth tokens
M|error-tracking|- Raw API keys or secrets
M|error-tracking|- IP addresses (in logs — rate limiting uses IP but doesn't log it)
M|error-tracking|**Acceptable to log:**
M|error-tracking|- `user_id` (UUID only — not email, not name)
M|error-tracking|- `venture_slug`
M|error-tracking|- `route` and `method`
M|error-tracking|- HTTP status code
M|error-tracking|- A generic user-safe message string
M|error-tracking|```typescript
M|error-tracking|export async function POST(req: NextRequest) {
M|error-tracking|const ventureSlug = req.headers.get('x-vtr-slug') ?? 'unknown'
M|error-tracking|try {
M|error-tracking|// ... handler logic
M|error-tracking|} catch (err) {
M|error-tracking|logError({
M|error-tracking|type: 'route_error',
M|error-tracking|route: '/api/[route-name]',
M|error-tracking|method: 'POST',
M|error-tracking|message: 'An unexpected error occurred.',
M|error-tracking|venture_slug: ventureSlug
M|error-tracking|})
M|error-tracking|return NextResponse.json(
M|error-tracking|{ error: 'An unexpected error occurred. Please try again.' },
M|error-tracking|{ status: 500 }
M|error-tracking|)
M|error-tracking|}
M|error-tracking|}
M|error-tracking|```
M|error-tracking|```typescript
M|error-tracking|const { data, error } = await supabase.from('table').select('...')
M|error-tracking|if (error) {
M|error-tracking|logError({
M|error-tracking|type: 'db_error',
M|error-tracking|route: '/api/[route-name]',
M|error-tracking|method: 'GET',
M|error-tracking|message: 'Database query failed.',
M|error-tracking|venture_slug: ventureSlug
M|error-tracking|})
M|error-tracking|return NextResponse.json(
M|error-tracking|{ error: 'Service temporarily unavailable. Please try again.' },
M|error-tracking|{ status: 503, headers: { 'Retry-After': '5' } }
M|error-tracking|)
M|error-tracking|}
M|error-tracking|```
M|error-tracking|```typescript
M|error-tracking|try {
M|error-tracking|const result = await apifyClient.actor('...').call(input)
M|error-tracking|} catch (err) {
M|error-tracking|logError({
M|error-tracking|type: 'external_api_error',
M|error-tracking|route: '/api/cp',
M|error-tracking|method: 'POST',
M|error-tracking|message: 'External data service unavailable.',
M|error-tracking|venture_slug: ventureSlug
M|error-tracking|})
M|error-tracking|// Return cached data if available, or degraded state
M|error-tracking|return NextResponse.json(
M|error-tracking|{ data: cachedData ?? null, degraded: true, error: 'Using cached data — live data temporarily unavailable.' },
M|error-tracking|{ status: cachedData ? 200 : 503 }
M|error-tracking|)
M|error-tracking|}
M|error-tracking|```